The paper deals with image segmentation, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of stochastic watershed hierarchies is a technique often used in computer graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM) for image processing. The paper also mentions the use of evaluation scores to select the best hierarchy, which suggests the involvement of machine learning (cs.AI) or statistical methods (cs.LG).
